<TITLE> Govt to remove import duty to lower edible oil prices </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to withdraw import duty on refined oil to curb the high prices of edible oil, finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said Sunday. Azizul broke the news to reporters after a meeting with the visiting IMF delegation at the planning ministry. The National Board of Revenue (NBR) chairman, Mohammad Abdul Majid, was present during the briefing. The NBR will issue a circular in a couple of days. "The prices of edible oil have started falling in the market, but the 10 percent import duty will be completely withdrawn to further lower the prices. The NBR will issue a circular in this regard in a day or two." He said import duties on different commodities including rice had already been lowered to zero to bring the essentials prices within the reach of common people. This time import duty on refined edible oil is being completely withdrawn." He hoped that the measure would help oil price fall in the market. In the retail market, the prices of soybean had been set at Tk 106.5 and palm oil at Tk 99.5 per kg. But the measure failed to curb the soaring prices of edible o
